<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-6635] Producer close does not await pending transaction</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-6635</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently close() only awaits completion of pending produce requests. If there is a transaction ongoing, it may be dropped. For example, if one thread is calling &lt;tt&gt;commitTransaction()&lt;/tt&gt; and another calls &lt;tt&gt;close()&lt;/tt&gt;, then the commit may never happen even if the caller is willing to wait for it (by using a long timeout). What&apos;s more, the thread blocking in &lt;tt&gt;commitTransaction()&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;will be stuck since the result will not be completed once the producer has shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
